@node "Main Window" "SLIPCall Users Guide"

@{b} Main Window
 ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{ub}

 Buttons
 ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
 @{" Dial    " link "Main Action Dial" 0}

    Tries to establish a connection with your internet provider.


 @{" Poll    " link "Main Action Poll" 0}

    Tries to establish a connection with your internet provider, execute
    your mail commands, hangup and quit.


 @{" Resume  " link "Main Action Resume" 0}

    Tries to resume a lost connection. (i.e. due to a system crash...)


 @{" Hang Up " link "Main Action Hangup" 0}

    Tries to hangup the line and quit AmiTCP.

 @{" Hide    " link "Main Project Hide" 0}

    Works just like any commodity. Hides SLIPCall, and it can be
    brought to front by either using `Commodities Exchange' or pressing
    it's Hotkeys.

  @{b}Abort@{ub}   

    Tries to abort current action, such as dialing or waiting.

    When dialing, abort will immediatly abort dialing, and return to
    initial state.

    When waiting, abort will cancel the waiting, and begin next redial.

 @{" Quit    " link "Main Project Quit" 0}

    Quit SLIPCall. If you're still online SLIPCall will ask you to
    confirm.

    When waiting for redial, Quit will immediatly abort waiting and redialing,
    and return to initial state.


 Info
 ŻŻŻŻ
  @{b}IP@{ub}      

    Your current IP address.

  @{b}Name@{ub}    

    The current name of your machine on the net.

  @{b}Status@{ub}  

    Information of what's happening.



@endnode

